{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_118","type":"agent_message","text":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- Added `RetryPolicy` defaults for all `FailureClass` values and threaded it through the standard-flow engine with a configurable remediation-cycle cap.\n- Refactored the engine into attempt-level execution plus post-success branching so retries, remediation, prompt-review pause, conditional approvals, and resume all happen at durable stage boundaries.\n- Added `StageContract::evaluate_permissive()` and moved non-passing review handling into the engine so QA/review payloads are persisted before remediation or terminal decisions.\n- Extended `StubBackendAdapter` with transient failures and staged payload overrides to support deterministic retry/remediation/resume tests.\n- Tightened run-snapshot semantics so only `running` may retain `active_run`; `paused`, `failed`, and `completed` now require `active_run == null`.\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- None functionally.\n- Added staged payload overrides to `StubBackendAdapter` beyond the required transient-failure helper to keep workflow-engine tests deterministic.\n\n## Testing\n- Verified compilation with `nix develop -c cargo check`.\n- Verified the full suite with `nix develop -c cargo test`.\n\n---"}}
